FGh3HA1UKPhE&d=bW%2FimIc%2BBhL52Hx1BZusr5Khd8YmQljH21R%2F5cbT5WU%3D&h=98c51178\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://youtu.be/Gh3HA1UKPhE</a>"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-10-22T03:43:34.000Z","msg":"呢條友不嬲唔係好可信"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-22T04:15:49.000Z","msg":"佢講講下拉埋去居歐權/EU citizen，明明英國已經脫歐<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"2e7eec3aa35d8174edfd425e8f35593b57db703e","tid":2235853,"uid":115184,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"45ac53d68aec9985f1180fe81a2d7784dfdef339","tid":2235853,"uid":115184,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-10-22T04:02:52.000Z","msg":"我睇咗條 bill ，重點只有2個：<br />\n1. 所有香港永久居民可以註冊成BNO<br />\n2. BNO有居英權 (right of adobe)"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-22T04:23:40.000Z","msg":"入面有一個好大漏洞，會被共匪利用：<br />\n<br />\n&quot;who is a permanent resident of Hong Kong&quot;<br />\n<br />\n漏洞係佢用咗現在式。我即刻發咗 email 去表達擔憂，大家可以參考：<br />\n<br />\nDear Mr Carmichael,<br />\n<br />\nI am a Hong Kong citizen. I am writing to express my concern about the &quot;Hong <br />\nKong Bill&quot; which will be put to the House of Common for 2nd reading this <br />\nFriday.<br />\n<br />\nMy concern is in Part 2 (Immigration), article 4(1). The text states that &quot;The <br />\nSecretary of State must, on an application made for the purpose, register as a <br />\nBritish National (Overseas) any person who is a permanent resident of<br />\nHong Kong.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nHowever, not all permanent residents of Hong Kong have a relationship to the <br />\nBritish colony of Hong Kong before 1997. For example, those who migrated to <br />\nHong Kong after 1997 and established their permanent residency after 7 years <br />\nof continuous residence, most of them are mainland China migrants. The <br />\ncommunity in Hong Kong think that they should not be entitled to take <br />\nadvantage of this offer because they do not have relationship to British Hong <br />\nKong, and they may pose a national security threat to the United Kingdom.<br />\n<br />\nTherefore, I suggest that the bill to be amended such that only &quot;those who <br />\nwere permanent residents of Hong Kong on 30 June 1997&quot; and their descendants <br />\n(if born outside Hong Kong, limited to one generation) can register as a <br />\nBritish National (Overseas). This will ensure that those who can register has <br />\na relationship to British Hong Kong.<br />\n<br />\nI would appreciate an amendment to be proposed.<br />\n<br />\nYours sincerely,"}]}